The paper discusses a novel model for machine comprehension of text, which falls under the category of natural language processing. The paper proposes an end-to-end neural model that outperforms previous neural models on machine comprehension benchmarks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing. Additionally, the paper also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), neural networks (cs.NE), and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques, which are all relevant sub-categories.
